## What is an mutator method?

An **mutator method** changes the value assigned to an instance variable

For example, the `public`(#e7e8ea) **mutator method** `setTitle`(#e7e8ea) allows other classes to modify the current value of the `private`(#e7e8ea) **instance variable** `title`(#e7e8ea).

```
public class Song {
  private String title;

  public void setTitle(String newTitle) {
    title = newTitle;
  }
}
```

The method is `public`(#e7e8ea) so it can be accessed from outside of the class. The return type is `void`(#e7e8ea) since it
doesn't return a value. The name of the method is typically `set`(#e7e8ea) followed by the name of the instance variable. We specify a parameter that matches the type of the instance variable.
